OL,3,CWhy the IFS thinks Labour and the
OL,4,CTories are being dishonest
OL,6,FIf the Office for Budget
OL,7,FResponsibility's forecasts prove
OL,8,Faccurate, then inflation will fade
OL,9,Ffurther, growth will pick up a little
OL,10,Fand living standards will soon begin
OL,11,Frising.
OL,13,FBy the next general election, a
OL,14,Fgrowing number of people should be
OL,15,Ffeeling a little better off.
OL,17,FBut whoever forms the next government
OL,18,Fwill inherit the toughest outlook for
OL,19,Fthe public finances in 80 years,
OL,20,Faccording the Institute for Fiscal
OL,21,FStudies (IFS).
