OL,3,CWhy the IFS thinks Labour and the
OL,4,CTories are being dishonest
OL,6,F"Government and opposition are joining
OL,7,Fin a conspiracy of silence in not
OL,8,Facknowledging the scale for the
OL,9,Fchoices and trade-offs that will face
OL,10,Fus after the election," said Paul
OL,11,FJohnson, Director of the IFS.
OL,13,F"They, and we, could be in for a rude
OL,14,Fawakening when those choices become
OL,15,Funavoidable".
OL,17,FThe chancellor delivered a chunky tax
OL,18,Fcut yesterday but it is a tax cut that
OL,19,Fis being paid for at the expense of
OL,20,Fspending on public services through
OL,21,Fthe next parliament.
