OL,3,CWhy the IFS thinks Labour and the
OL,4,CTories are being dishonest
OL,6,FIf your pay was growing strongly you
OL,7,Fmight not be too concerned. If your
OL,8,Fincome wasn't growing then you'd have
OL,9,Fa problem.
OL,11,FAnd the government has a debt problem.
OL,12,FSlow economic growth means tax income
OL,13,Fhaven't been growing.
OL,15,FMeanwhile, the government has taken on
OL,16,Fa much bigger mortgage, borrowing
OL,17,Fmoney in order to keep people in their
OL,18,Fjobs during Covid lockdowns and to
OL,19,Fsubside energy bills during a cost of
OL,20,Fliving crisis.
