OL,3,CWhy the IFS thinks Labour and the
OL,4,CTories are being dishonest
OL,6,F"This was not a budget which addressed
OL,7,Fthe real challenges we are facing
OL,8,Fbecause it was not transparent about
OL,9,Fwhat those challenges are," says
OL,10,FJohnson.
OL,12,FThe IFS argues that if the
OL,13,FConservatives wish to cut taxes and
OL,14,Fbelieve there are some services the
OL,15,Fstate should no longer be providing
OL,16,Fthen they should say so publicly.
OL,18,FEqually, if Labour thinks public
OL,19,Fservices are on the ropes and need
OL,20,Fbetter funding they should be honest
OL,21,Fabout which taxes they will increase.
